      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name will be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code will be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and will have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List will go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java.

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name will be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Using Manifest, JarOutputStream, Paths, JavaCompiler

        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        jarFile - target .jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.
